Here's is a list of the most preferred textbooks for Computer Science & Information Technology branch...


Section # 1 : Computer Science and Information Technology


  Algorithms

		(1) Introduction to Algorithms - by Cormen, Leiserson, Rivest & Stein


	Compiler Design

		(1) Compilers: Principles, Techniques, and Tools - by Aho, Sethi & Ullman


	Computer Networks

		(1) Computer Networking, A Top-Down Approach Featuring the Internet - by Kurose & Ross
		(2) Computer Networks, A Systems Approach - by Peterson & Davie


	Computer Organization and Architecture

		(1) Computer Organization and Architecture: Designing for Performance - by Stallings
		(2) Computer Organization - by Hamacher, Vranesic & Zaky


	Databases

		(1) Fundamentals of Database Systems - by Elmasri & Navathe


	Digital Logic

		(1) Digital Design - by Morris Mano


	Information Systems and Software Engineering

		(1) Software Engineering: A Practitioner's Approach - by Pressman


	Operating System

		(1) Operating Systems, Internals and Design Principles - by Stallings
		(2) Operating System Concepts - by Silberschatz, Galvin & Gagne


	Programming and Data Structures

		(1) Handbook of Data Structures and Applications - by Mehta & Sahni
		(2) The C Programming Language - by Kernighan & Ritchie


	Theory of Computation

		(1) Introduction to Automata Theory, Languages & Computation - by Hopcroft, Motwani & Ullman
		(2) Introduction to Computer Theory - by Daniel Cohen
		(3) An Introduction to Formal Languages and Automata - by Peter Linz


	Web technologies

		Refer good websites as per its syllabus.


-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------


Section # 2 : Engineering Mathematics


	Calculus

		(1) Calculus, Schaum's Outlines - by Ayres & Mendelson
		(2) Calculus, The Easy Way - by Douglas Downing


	Graph Theory

		(1) Graph Theory - by Narsingh Deo


	Linear Algebra

		(1) Algebra - by Michael Artin
		(2) Introduction to Linear Algebra - by Gilbert Strang


	Combinatorics, Mathematical Logic, Probability, Set Theory & Algebra

		(1) Elements of Discrete Mathematics - by Liu
		(2) Discrete Mathematical Structures with Applications to Computer Science - by Tremblay & Manohar
		(3) Discrete Mathematics & Its Applications - by Rosen


	Numerical Methods

		(1) Numerical Methods - by Rajaraman


-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------


Section # 3 : General Aptitude


	(1) Quantitative Aptitude - by R. S. Agarwal
	(2) Barron's GRE - by Green & Wolf
	(3) When Bad Grammar Happens to Good People - by Ann Batko
	(4) English Grammar and Composition - by Wren and Martin
